definition: ordinal number/day of a month/mark/sign/business establishment/size/ship suffix/horn (wind instrument)/bugle call/assumed name/to take a pulse/classifier used to indicate number of people

sentences.english: The flywheels of some engines also carry marks indicating the serial numbers of the cylinders where the compression occurs.

sentences.english: Subrange types maintain the ordinalities of their base types.
sentences.chinese: 子界类型保留了其基类型的序号。
那些钱有序号的对不对？

sentences.english: Any gaps in the sequence will indicate the books that have not yet been returned.
sentences.chinese: 顺序号中的任何间隔将表示尚未归还的图书。

sentences.english: The first method is to generate a name using a sequence number.
sentences.chinese: 第一种方法是使用序号生成名称。

sentences.english: You are not using consecutive start position numbers.
sentences.chinese: 你必须使用连续的出生地点序号。

sentences.english: Sequence number assigned to the issue.
sentences.chinese: 分配给每个变更请求一个顺序号。

sentences.english: This is the original order, which is found also in Num.
sentences.chinese: 这是原来的秩序，这是公司还发现，在序号。

sentences.english: Circle the number next to the correct answer.
sentences.chinese: 把正确答案的序号画圈。

sentences.chinese: 你必须使用连续的出生地点序号。

sentences.english: Be sure to click on each number so you can see all of the photos.
sentences.chinese: 一定要点击那些序号，这样你就能看到所有的图片。

sentences.english: Creates a new column mapping, using column ordinals to refer to source and destination columns.
sentences.chinese: 创建新的列映射，并使用列序号引用源列和目标列。

sentences.english: Item No. is refers to the order of this type of commodity in this customs declaration form.
sentences.chinese: 项号指该类货物在本报关单中的序号。

sentences.english: If you do not specify a sequence number, the system retrieves the most recently run command.
sentences.chinese: 如果不指定序号，那么系统会检索最近运行的命令。

sentences.english: After the athletes enter the arena, they must start the competition according to the Order Card.
sentences.chinese: 运动员入场后，按各组别各单项的序号上场比赛。
